==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: man-hour
<hw>man-hour</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quantity of work which one person can perform in one hour; -- often an
estimate made for the purpose of deciding whether to undertake a
project, and sometimes used in accounting; <as>as, it will take a
hundred <ex>man-hours</ex> to write the program</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manhunt</ent>⟦br⟧
